<P>A DISCOURSE Delivered before an A&s;&s;embly OF FREE and ACCEPTED MASONS, Convened for the purpo&s;e of In&s;talling a LODGE in the City of NORWICH, in CONNECTICUT, on the Fe&s;tival of ST. JOHN the BAPTIST, 1795.</P>
<Q><HI>Prove all things; hold fa&s;t that which is good.</HI>
<BIBL>1. The&s;. v. 21.</BIBL></Q>
<P>By SAMUEL SEABURY. D. D. Bi&s;hop of Connecticut and Rhode-I&s;land.</P>
<P><HI>NORWICH:</HI> PRINTED BY BROTHER JOHN STERRY AND CO. M, DCC, XV.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="resolution">
<PB REF="029480_0002_0FE13BC994636028">
<P>FESTIVAL of St. John the Bapti&s;t, 24th of June, Anne Lucis, 5795.</P>
<P>At a &s;pecial Grand Lodge of Free and accepted Ma&s;ons, held at Norwich in the State of Connecticut, pre&s;ent the Mo&s;t Wor&s;hipful ELIPHALET BULKLEY Grand Ma&s;ter pro. tem.</P>
<P>VOTED, that the thanks of this Lodge be given to Brother SAMUEL SEABURY, for his di&s;cour&s;e delivered at their reque&s;t this day; and that Brothers JOSHUA COIT, ASA SPALDING and EBENEZER HUNTINGTON, be a Committee to wait on him and de&s;ire a copy for the pre&s;s,</P>
<CLOSER>Extract from the minutes.
<SIGNED>Te&s;t SAM. HUNTINGTON 3rd, Sec.ry <HI>pro. tem.</HI></SIGNED></CLOSER>
</DIV1>
